sy%20is%20continuinfg%20over%20the%20two%20nomenclatures.%20The%20Opposition%20has%20slammed%20the%20BJP-led%20government%20at%20the%20Centre%2C%20accusing%20it%20of%20rebranding%20India%20only%20for%20political%20reasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20India%20Got%20Its%20Name%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20many%20are%20aware%20that%20the%20name%20Bharat%20wasn't%20in%20the%20first%20draft%20of%20the%20Indian%20Constitution%20when%20it%20was%20introduced%20by%20Dr%20B%20R%20Ambedkar%2C%20the%20Chairman%20of%20the%20drafting%20committee%2C%20on%20November%204%2C%201948.%20In%20fact%2C%20it%20wasn't%20until%20a%20year%20later%20when%20the%20finalisation%20of%20the%20Constitution%20approached%20that%20the%20omission%20of%20the%20native%20name%20was%20underlined%20by%20many%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20this%2C%20on%20September%2018%2C%201949%2C%20Dr.%20Ambedkar%20moved%20an%20amendment%20to%20draft%20Article%201%2C%20which%20read%2C%20%26quot%3BIndia%2C%20that%20is%2C%20Bharat%20shall%20be%20a%20Union%20of%20States.%26quot%3B%20The%20phraseology%20came%20under%20criticism%20from%20assembly%20member%20HV%20Kamath%2C%20who%20called%20it%20%26quot%3Bclumsy%20and%20a%20constitutional%20error%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHeated%20Debate%20And%20Alternatives%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Floksabha.nic.in%2Fwritereaddata%2Fcadebatefiles%2FC18091949.html%5C%22%3EHV%20Kamath%20%3C%2Fa%3Ethen%20offered%20two%20alternatives%3A%20%26quot%3BBharat%2C%20or%2C%20in%20the%20English%20language%2C%20India%2C%20shall%20be%20a%20Union%20of%20States%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BHind%2C%20or%2C%20in%20the%20English%20language%2C%20India%2C%20shall%20be%20a%20Union%20of%20States.%26quot%3B%20He%20said%20that%20the%20phrase%20%26quot%3Bin%20the%20English%20language%2C%20India%26quot%3B%20was%20critical%2C%20for%20in%20many%20countries%2C%20the%20nation%20was%20still%20known%20as%20%26quot%3BHindustan%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20its%20people%20were%20referred%20to%20as%20Hindus%20regardless%20of%20their%20faith.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20heated%20discussion%20ensued%20with%20several%20members%20of%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20registering%20their%20disapproval%20of%20the%20name%20India%20and%20arguing%20in%20favour%20of%20Bharat.%20For%20instance%2C%20Seth%20Govind%20Das%20from%20Jabalpur%20backed%20HV%20Kamath%20saying%2C%20%E2%80%9CIndia%2C%20that%20is%2C%20Bharat%E2%80%9D%20weren't%20the%20most%20pleasing%20words%20for%20the%20name%20of%20a%20country%2C%20adding%20it%20should%20be%2C%20%E2%80%9CBharat%20known%20as%20India%20also%20in%20foreign%20countries%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20draw%20his%20point%20home%2C%20HV%20Kamath%20referred%20to%20the%20Irish%20constitution%20and%20how%20the%20lawmakers%20named%20their%20country.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Constitution%20of%20the%20Irish%20Free%20State%20reads%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20name%20of%20the%20State%20is%20Eire%2C%20or%2C%20in%20the%20English%20language%2C%20Ireland%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Floksabha.nic.in%2Fwritereaddata%2Fcadebatefiles%2FC18091949.html%5C%22%3EHV%20Kamath%20said.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EWhile%20Seth%20Govind%20Das%20Das%20argued%20that%20Vishnu%20Purana%20and%20Brahma%20Purana%20mentioned%20Bharat%2C%20other%20members%20claimed%20that%20the%20seventh-century%20Chinese%20traveller%20Hiuen%20Tsang%20also%20called%20the%20country%20Bharat%20and%20not%20India.%20Many%20also%20said%20that%20India%20wasn't%20an%20ancient%20word%2C%20unlike%20Bharat%2C%20which%20epitomised%20the%20history%20and%20culture%20of%20this%20civilisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EHargovind%20Pant%2C%20who%20represented%20the%20United%20Provinces%2C%20said%20that%20he%20failed%20to%20understand%20why%20the%20word%20'Bharat%20Varsha'%20was%20not%20acceptable%20to%20the%20House%20when%20%26quot%3Bthe%20importance%20and%20glory%20of%20this%20word%20is%20