s%2C%20thanks%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fancestrydna-genetic-test-review-ancestry-update-2019-2%5C%22%3EDNA%20analysis%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Berlin's%20Museums%20authority%20(SPK)%20said%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20discovery%20of%20descendants%2C%20made%20by%20Berlin's%20Museum%20of%20Prehistory%20and%20Early%20History%2C%20was%20lauded%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.preussischer-kulturbesitz.de%2Fpressemitteilung%2Fartikel%2F2023%2F09%2F05%2Fmenschliche-ueberreste-aus-tansania-erstmals-bestaetigung-von-verwandtschaftsverhaeltnissen-zu-lebenden-personen.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bsmall%20miracle%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20SPK's%20director%20said%20in%20a%20translated%20press%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20is%20part%20of%20a%20wider-ranging%20project%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fafrica.businessinsider.com%2Flocal%2Flifestyle%2Fgermany-is-considering-returning-some-artefacts-stolen-from-nigeria-during-the%2Fjj9nhjs%5C%22%3Eby%20the%20museum%20to%20find%20the%20provenance%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20at%20least%201%2C100%20skulls%20found%20in%20a%207%2C700-strong%20skull%20collection%20the%20museum%20acquired%20from%20Berlin's%20Charit%C3%A9%20Hospital%20museum%20in%202011.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20collection%20is%20controversial%20because%20of%20its%20origins.%20At%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%2020th%20century%2C%20the%20German%20empire%20took%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-africa-46277158%5C%22%3E%C2%A0thousands%20of%20skulls%20from%3C%2Fa%3E%20its%20colonies%20for%20research%20into%20racial%20classification.%20Such%20research%20has%20since%20been%20discredited%2C%20the%20BBC%20reported%20in%202018.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20these%20skulls%C2%A0are%20thought%20to%20have%20found%20their%20way%20into%20the%20SPK's%20collection%2C%20per%20the%20BBC.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20these%20skulls%20were%20from%20colonial%20victims.%20As%20part%20of%20the%20restitution%20efforts%2C%20the%20SPK%20has%20previously%20returned%2020%20of%20the%20collection's%20skulls%20to%20Namibia%20in%202011.%20These%20are%20thought%20to%20have%20belonged%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.science.org%2Fcontent%2Farticle%2Fgermany-returns-colonial-era-skulls-namibia%5C%22%3Eindigenous%20Nama%20and%20Herero%20tribes%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20were%20killed%20in%20brutal%20wars%20by%20German%20invaders%20almost%20a%20century%20earlier%2C%20Science%20Magazine%20reported%20in%202011.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20DNA%20sample%20provided%20a%20direct%20match%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20the%20skulls%20in%20the%20collection%20were%20in%20very%20poor%20condition%20when%20they%20were%20acquired%20by%20the%20SPK%2C%20and%20many%20lacked%20conservation%20records%2C%20which%20is%20why%20it%20is%20so%20difficult%20to%20trace%20the%20skulls%20back%20to%20descendants%2C%20a%20museum%20spokesperson%20told%20Insider%20on%20the%20phone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20clues%20to%20help%20with%20the%20identification%20of%20some%20of%20these%20remains.%20Diary%20entries%20and%20records%2C%20as%20well%20as%20numbers%20or%20words%20unceremoniously%20scribbled%20on%20some%20of%20the%20skulls%2C%20helped%20narrow%20down%20their%20origins.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20case%20of%20eight%20of%20the%20skulls%2C%20the%20museum%20collected%20enough%20information%20to%20seek%20out%20potential%20relatives.%20They%20contacted%2010%20people%20to%20provide%20DNA%20swabs.%20Surprisingly%2C%20one%20was%20a%20perfect%20match.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fact%20that%20the%20skull%20was%20traced%20back%20to%20a%20descendent%20is%20%26quot%3Bamazing%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20museum%20spokesperson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20person's%20ancestor%20had%20a%20single%20word%20inscribed%20on%20his%20skull%3A%20%26quot%3BAkida.%26quot%3B%20Per%20the%20museum's%20statement%2C%20this%20suggests%20this%20person%20was%20a%20very%20important%20person%20for%20the%20Chagga%20people%2C%20a%20people%20from%20the%20Kilimanjaro%20Region%20of%20Tanzania.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20SPK%20believes%20this%20person%20was%20a%20high-ranking%20advisor%20to%20Mangi%20Meli%2C%20the%20ruler%20of%20the%20Chagga%20people.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20clear%20what%20would%20have%20happened%20to%20this%20advisor%20at%20the%20time%20of%20his%20death.%20But%20we%20do%20know%20Meli%20met%20a%20brutal%20end%20when%20he%20was%20hanged%20and%20decapitated%20after%20leading%20an%20uprising%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.preussischer-kulturbesitz.de%2Fen%2Fnews-detail%2Farticle%2F2019%2F09%2F20%2Fschaedel-des-mangi-meli-nicht-in-spk-sammlung0.html%5C%22%3Eagainst%20German%20invaders%20in%201900%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20per%20the%20BBC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20other%20skulls%20have%20also%20been%20traced%20back%20to%20people%20who%20provided%20DNA%20samples%2C%20and%20it%20is%20%26quot%3Blikely%26quot%3B%20that%20they%20are%20descendants%2C%20per%20the%20statement.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20relatives%20will%20now%20be%20contacted%20to%20determine%20what%20they%20want%20to%20do%20with%20the%20remains.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmuseum-traces-skull-pillaged-german-colonizers-back-descendant-africa-tanzania-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694001097000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f847aea35dd100195edd2d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmuseum-traces-skull-pillaged-german-colonizers-back-descendant-africa-tanzania-2023-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20German%20museum%20says%20it%20is%20ready%20to%20return%20the%20human%20skulls%20from%20East%20Africa%2C%20which%20were%20removed%20under%20German%20colonial%20rule.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mguenot%40businessinsider.com%20(Marianne%20Guenot)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A58%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmuseum-traces-skull-pillaged-german-colonizers-back-descendant-africa-tanzania-2023-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20CAG's%20Mizoram%20Audit%20Report%20Leads%20to%20Numerous%20Questions%2C%20Some%20on%20its%20Own%20Processes%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F06163312%2FCAG-building-II.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20August%2023%2C%20the%20Mizoram%20state%20assembly%20witnessed%20the%20presentation%20of%20an%20audit%20report%20by%20the%20Comptroller%20and%20Auditor%20General%20(CAG)%20on%20Mizoram%20state%20for%20the%20financial%20year%20ending%20on%20March%2031%2C%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20was%20shared%20with%20the%20state%20government%20on%20February%2024%2C%202023%2C%20but%20it%20took%20almost%20six%20months%20for%20the%20state%20government%20to%20schedule%20the%20presentation%20of%20the%20report%20before%20the%20state%20assembly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWas%20the%20opposition%20concerned%20by%20such%20a%20prolonged%20delay%3F%20Did%20any%20MLA%20raise%20a%20question%20about%20the%20audit%20report%20being%20finalised%20but%20not%20yet%20in%20the%20public%20domain%3F%20Did%20any%20citizen%20file%20an%20RTI%20application%20with%20governor%E2%80%99s%20office%20or%20with%20the%20office%20of%20the%20principal%20accountant%20general%20to%20seek%20the%20information%20on%20this%20finalised%20report%20that%20was%20not%20yet%20in%20the%20public%20domain%20till%20August%2023%2C%202023%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20our%20constitutional%20democracy%2C%20have%20such%20questions%20lost%20relevance%3F%20Or%20have%20they%20been%20reduced%20to%20rhetorical%20questions%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIdeally%2C%20one%20would%20imagine%20that%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98supreme%20audit%20institute%E2%80%99%20shall%20feel%20morally%20obliged%20to%20at%20least%20share%20the%20status%20of%20such%20%E2%80%98finalised%20but%20not%20yet%20in%20the%20public%20domain%E2%80%99%20audit%20reports%20on%20its%20website%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcag.gov.in%2Fen%2Fstatus-of-audit-reports%5C%22%3EStatus%20of%20Audit%20Reports%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99%20webpage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20looking%20through%20this%20webpage%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20quite%20help.%20For%20some%20curious%20reason%2C%20the%20CAG%20seems%20to%20be%20saying%20that%20only%20the%20Telangana%20state%20government%20appears%20to%20have%20got%20four%20such%20%E2%80%98finalised%20but%20not%20yet%20in%20the%20public%20domain%E2%80%99%20audit%20reports.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReading%20Mizoram%E2%80%99s%20latest%20audit%20report%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20now%20in%20the%20public%20domain%20after%20having%20been%20presented%20in%20the%20Mizoram%20assembly%20%E2%80%93%20and%20what%20it%20has%20reported%20on%20a%20welfare%20fund%20meant%20for%20providing%20some%20semblance%20of%20social%20protection%20for%20construction%20workers%20makes%20one%20wonder%20if%20CAG%20auditors%20have%20failed%20to%20ask%20some%20pertinent%20accountability%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20article%20engages%20with%20the%20fiscal%20data%20on%20the%20Mizoram%20Building%20and%20Other%20Construction%20Workers%E2%80%99%20Welfare%20Fund%20(MBOCWWF)%2C%20compiled%20from%20similar%20audit%20reports%20over%20the%20last%20nine%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22NHAI's%20Tolls%2C%20UDAN%20Delays%2C%20Unsanctioned%20Railway%20Costs%3A%20What%20the%20CAG%20Reports%20Say%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcag-report-nhai-toll-collection-railway-bharatmala-udan%5C%22%3ENHAI%E2%80%99s%20Tolls%2C%20UDAN%20Delays%2C%20Unsanctioned%20Railway%20Costs%3A%20What%20the%20CAG%20Reports%20Say%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20chapter%204%20of%20the%20latest%20report%2C%20wherein%20CAG%20auditors%20have%20made%20observations%20on%20the%20%E2%80%98quality%20of%20accounts%20and%20financial%20reporting%20practices%E2%80%99%2C%20readers%20are%20told%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20Building%20and%20Other%20Construction%20Workers%E2%80%99%20Welfare%20Cess%20is%20the%20only%20cess%20currently%20being%20collected%20by%20%5Bthe%5D%20government%20of%20Mizoram%20allowed%20under%20the%20Building%20and%20Other%20Construction%20Workers%E2%80%99%20Welfare%20Cess%20Act%20%5BBOCW%20Act%5D%2C%201996%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20two%20subsequent%20paragraphs%2C%20CAG%20auditors%20have%20presented%20data%20in%20two%20tables%20that%20respectively%20inform%20us%20on%20(i)%20membership%20enrolment%20in%20the%20Construction%20Workers%E2%80%99%20Welfare%20Board%20(MBOCWWB)%20and%20(ii)%20the%20position%20of%20cess%20collection%2C%20other%20receipts%20and%20actual%20expenditure%20incurred%20during%20the%20last%20five%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20these%20tables%20are%20said%20to%20be%20sourced%20from%20the%20MBOCWWF.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20in%20the%20past%2C%20CAG%20auditors%20had%20voiced%20qualitative%20comments%20after%20presenting%20such%20statistics%2C%20the%20CAG%E2%80%99s%20audit%20report%20for%20the%20fiscal%20year%202021-22%20appears%20to%20be%20silent%20on%20any%20qualitative%20remarks%20whatsoever.%20We%20are%20told%20in%20a%20matter-of-fact%20style%20the%20following%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CMBOCWWB%20received%20INR%2028.68%20crore%20during%20the%20year%202021-22%2C%20out%20of%20which%20INR%2022.88%20crore%20was%20cess%20received%20during%20the%20year.%20During%20the%20year%2C%20the%20Board%20spent%20an%20amount%20of%20INR%2029.30%20crore%20on%20administrative%20expenses%20and%20welfare%20schemes%2Fbenefits%20as%20envisaged%20in%20the%20%5BBOCW%20Act%5D.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShould%20CAG%20auditors%20merely%20reproduce%20the%20data%20tables%20furnished%20to%20them%20by%20the%20executive%20during%20the%20audit%20process%3F%20Or%20should%20they%20read%2C%20interpret%20and%20analyse%20these%20data%20tables%20to%20report%20to%20citizens%20whether%20the%20executive%20has%20complied%20with%20prescribed%20guidelines%20contained%20in%20the%20governing%20law%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20my%20opinion%2C%20CAG%20auditors%20should%20have%20pressed%20the%20MBOCWWB%20to%20furnish%20a%20scheme-wise%20breakup%20as%20well%20as%20details%20on%20administrative%20expenditure%20for%20the%20Rs%2029.30%20crore%20that%20is%20shown%20in%20one%20of%20its%20tables%20as%20total%20expenditure%20(see%20below).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20expecting%20our%20national%20auditor%20to%20tell%20us%20this%2C%20we%20are%20not%20merely%20being%20pedantic%2C%20since%20one%20of%20the%20prerequisites%20of%20the%20BOCW%20Act%20is%20that%20out%20of%20its%20total%20annual%20expenditure%2C%2095%25%20should%20be%20towards%20welfare%20schemes%20and%20only%205%25%20can%20be%20on%20administrative%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fayushman-bharat-cag-report-pmjay-corruption%5C%22%3ETreatment%20for%20the%20Dead%2C%20Discharge%20Before%20Surgery%20and%20the%20Many%20Problems%20of%20Ayushman%20Bharat%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20also%20wish%20CAG%20auditors%20would%20see%20how%20their%20earlier%20audit%20paragraphs%20on%20the%20MBOCWWF%20read%20compared%20to%20this%20one.%20For%20example%2C%20the%20CAG%E2%80%99s%20audit%20report%20on%20Mizoram%20(state%20finance)%20for%20the%20fiscal%20year%202017-18%20had%20pointed%20out%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20can%20be%20seen%20from%20the%20table%20above%20that%20the%20fund%20position%20of%20the%20%5BMBOCWWB%5D%20in%20respect%20of%20receipt%20for%20the%20year%202017-18%20is%20INR%2017.89%20crore%20(INR%2015.08%20crore%20%2B%20INR%202.81%20crore)%2C%20and%20expenditure%20is%20INR%208.15%20crore.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHowever%2C%20as%20per%20statement%20of%20receipt%20and%20expenditure%20submitted%20(March%202019)%20by%20the%20Board%20for%202017-18%2C%20total%20receipt%20is%20INR%2017.89%20crore%20and%20total%20expenditure%20is%20INR%208.42%20crore.%20Hence%2C%20there%20was%20a%20difference%20of%20INR%200.27%20crore%20(INR%208.42%20crore%20minus%20INR%208.15%20crore)%2C%20which%20is%20required%20to%20be%20reconciled.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EFurther%2C%20out%20of%20total%20expenditure%20of%20INR%208.42%20crore%20depicted%20in%20the%20accounts%20for%20the%20year%202017-18%2C%20INR%206.30%20crore%20was%20shown%20as%20an%20unauthorised%20transaction%20by%20the%20bank.%20Hence%2C%20the%20actual%20expenditure%20of%20the%20Board%20for%20the%20year%202017-18%20would%20be%20INR%202.12%20crore%20(INR%208.42%20crore%20minus%20INR%206.30%20crore)%2C%20which%20needs%20to%20be%20rectified%20by%20the%20Board%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20while%20presenting%20their%20audit%20observation%20on%20the%20MBOCWWF%20for%20the%20fiscal%20year%202018-19%2C%20CAG%20auditors%20stated%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20is%20evident%20from%20the%20table%20above%2C%20the%20MBOCWB%20received%20INR%2039.98%20crore%20during%20the%20year%202018-19%2C%20and%20expended%20INR%2013.56%20crore%20(Administrative%20Expense%3A%20INR%200.39%20crore%2C%20Welfare%20schemes%3A%20INR%2012.76%20crore%20and%20Others%3A%20INR%200.41%20crore)%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20also%20makes%20readers%20and%20citizens%20concerned%20is%20that%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20audit%20observations%20in%20CAG%20reports%20on%20BOCW%20funds%20across%20the%20country%2C%20there%20are%20different%20styles%20of%20drafting%20audit%20observations%20for%20different%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20worrisome%20trend%20is%20that%20while%20ideally%2C%20state%20finance%20audit%20reports%20shall%20present%20an%20audit%20paragraph%20on%20this%20special-purpose%20social%20welfare%20fund%2C%20some%20recently%20tabled%20audit%20reports%20do%20not%20even%20have%20a%20very%20basic%20audit%20paragraph%20on%20this%20fund.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20the%20CAG%E2%80%99s%20audit%20report%20on%20Goa%20(state%20finance)%20for%20the%20year%20ended%20March%2031%2C%202022%20and%20tabled%20in%20the%20state%20assembly%20on%20August%2010%2C%202023%2C%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20have%20any%20information%20on%20Goa%E2%80%99s%20Building%20and%20Other%20Construction%20Workers%E2%80%99%20Welfare%20Fund.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20overall%20picture%20that%20emerges%20by%20comparing%20audit%20observations%20on%20the%20MBOCWWF%20from%20several%20audit%20reports%20can%20be%20presented%20in%20the%20tables%20below%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F4HXpb%2F3%2F%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22888%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Position%20of%20the%20MBOCWWF%20(2013-2019)%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22398%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FHLVX6%2F1%2F%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22888%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Position%20of%20the%20MBOCWWF%20(2017-2022)%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22348%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20we%20do%20not%20have%20the%20fiscal%20figures%20on%20the%20fund%20position%20of%20the%20MBOCWWB%20for%20the%20year%202012-13%2C%20we%20can%20safely%20assume%20that%20the%20cess%20receipts%20would%20not%20be%20very%20high%2C%20since%20the%20Mizoram%20state%20government%20had%20notified%20the%20enforcement%20of%20levy%20and%20collection%20of%20construction%20workers%E2%80%99%20welfare%20cess%20%3Cem%3Evide%3C%2Fem%3E%20office%20memorandum%20dated%20May%2029%2C%202012%20only.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20the%20overall%20picture%20that%20emerges%20by%20comparing%20the%20construction%20workers%E2%80%99%20enrolment%20data%20across%20the%20years%20is%20as%20presented%20below.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FYCQI0%2F2%2F%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22888%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Details%20of%20membership%20enrolment%20in%20the%20MBOCWWB%20(2016-2021)%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22321%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FzKToO%2F1%2F%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22888%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Details%20of%20membership%20enrolment%20in%20the%20MBOCWWB%20(2017-2022)%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22321%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20shocking%20manner%2C%20when%20we%20compare%20the%20number%20on%20construction%20workers%E2%80%99%20enrolment%20pertaining%20to%20the%20fiscal%20years%202019-20%20and%202020-21%20given%20in%20the%20CAG%E2%80%99s%20audit%20reports%20for%20the%20fiscal%20year%202020-21%20and%202021-22%2C%20those%20values%20undergo%20a%20massive%20shift%20that%20is%20completely%20unexplainable%20(highlighted%20in%20yellow).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWill%20CAG%20auditors%20revisit%20the%20claims%20presented%20in%20the%20audit%20paragraphs%20across%20these%20two%20reports%20and%20present%20the%20true%20picture%20for%20citizens%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fhimanshu123%5C%22%3EHimanshu%20Upadhyaya%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20at%20the%20School%20of%20Development%20Studies%2C%20Azim%20Premji%20University.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20content%20and%20opinions%20expressed%20are%20that%20of%20the%20author%2C%20and%20are%20not%20necessarily%20endorsed%20by%2Fdo%20not%20necessarily%20reflect%20the%20views%20of%20Azim%20Premji%20University.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694001055000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F06163312%2FCAG-building-II.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fquestions-cag-auditors-failed-to-probe-in-its-mizoram-report%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20its%20latest%20report%20on%20the%20Mizoram%20government%20%E2%80%93%20which%20remained%20finalised%20but%20out%20o