nt%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fchina%2Fchina-mulls-jail-and-fine-for-wearing-clothes-that-hurt-govts-sensibilities%2Farticleshow%2F103425454.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fchina%2Fchina-mulls-jail-and-fine-for-wearing-clothes-that-hurt-govts-sensibilities%2Famp_articleshow%2F103425454.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fchina%2Fchina-mulls-jail-and-fine-for-wearing-clothes-that-hurt-govts-sensibilities%2Famp_articleshow%2F103425454.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Hills%20Weren't%20Meant%20for%20Rapid%20'Development'%20%E2%80%93%20and%20So%20the%20Cracks%20Are%20Starting%20to%20Show%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F06135212%2FCityscape_of_Shimla.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20monsoon%20has%20virtually%20receded%20for%20this%20season%20in%20India%2C%20and%20therefore%20there%20is%20no%20possibility%20of%20rains%2C%20particularly%20torrential%20spells.%20We%20can%20now%20hope%20not%20to%20hear%20the%20depressing%20news%20of%20our%20crumbling%20hills%20and%20their%20habitat%20in%20the%20Himalayan%20region%2C%20at%20least%20till%20the%20next%20season.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20we%20cannot%20complain%20that%20we%20did%20not%20get%20warning%20signals.%20For%20the%20past%20several%20years%2C%20severe%20traffic%20jams%20to%20reach%20north%20Indian%20hill%20stations%20such%20as%20Nainital%20(and%20other%20Tal%20towns%20in%20proximity)%2C%20Shimla%20and%20Mussoorie%20have%20been%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20have%20spurred%20questions%20about%20the%20carrying%20capacity%20of%20our%20%E2%80%98hill%20stations%E2%80%99%2C%20and%20pressure%20is%20mounting%20for%20building%20regulations%20to%20control%20the%20unhindered%20concretisation%20across%20the%20Himalayan%20region%20in%20order%20to%20make%20the%20habitat%20sustainable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20had%20an%20%E2%80%98urban%E2%80%99%20tradition%20since%20the%20time%20of%20Mohenjo-daro%2C%20and%20its%20epics%20too%20speak%20of%20grand%20capital%20cities%2C%20but%20there%20is%20no%20word%20for%20%E2%80%98hill%20station%E2%80%99%20in%20any%20local%20dialect%2C%20indicating%20that%20the%20hills%20must%20have%20had%20human%20habitations%2C%20but%20no%20urban%20centres%20%E2%80%93%20small%2C%20medium%20or%20big.%20Obviously%2C%20there%20was%20no%20tradition%20of%20the%20kings%20running%20away%20to%20or%20maintaining%20a%20summer%20capital%20in%20the%20hills.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EColonial%20urban%20development%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20the%20history%20of%20Srinagar%20indicates%20that%20despite%20various%20dynasties%20ruling%20Kashmir%20over%20the%20centuries%2C%20urbanisation%20was%20slow%20to%20begin%20in%20the%20region%20described%20as%20a%20piece%20of%20heaven%20on%20Earth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Mughal%20rule%20since%201586%20witnessed%20development%20and%20growth%20in%20Srinagar.%20The%20Sikh%20empire%20since%201819%20did%20not%20add%20to%20the%20process%20of%20urbanisation%20in%20the%20hill%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20first%20Anglo-Sikh%20war%2C%20the%20British%2C%20under%20a%20treaty%20with%20Dogra%20monarch%20Gulab%20Singh%2C%20sold%20Kashmir%20for%20Rs%2075%20lakh%20in%201846.%20In%201872%2C%20Ranbir%20Singh%20began%20the%20tradition%20of%20having%20two%20capitals%20%E2%80%93%20Jammu%20(winter)%20and%20Srinagar%20(summer).%20And%20thus%20began%20the%20tradition%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98durbar%20move%E2%80%99%20as%20well%20as%20of%20having%20a%20capital%20in%20cool%20climes%20during%20the%20summer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20Kashmir%20%E2%80%93%20Srinagar%20in%20particular%2C%20but%20equally%20significantly%20Pahalgam%2C%20Gulmarg%20and%20other%20such%20smaller%20habitations%20too%20%E2%80%93%20developed%20to%20cater%20to%20the%20British%20colonisers%E2%80%99%20needs%20of%20beating%20heat%20in%20the%20north%20Indian%20plains%2C%20it%20does%20not%20represent%20an%20appropriate%20example%20of%20the%20colonial%20urban%20development%20in%20India%20that%20led%20to%20the%20emergence%20of%20hill%20stations%20in%20India%2C%20currently%20a%20craze%20for%20the%20expanding%20Indian%20middle%20class.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20hill%20stations%20sprouted%20in%20different%20regions%20a%20historical%20view%20gives%20a%20better%20view.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnthony%20D.%20King%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EColonial%20Urban%20Development%3A%20Culture%2C%20Social%20Power%20and%20Environment%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20classic%20on%20the%20subject%2C%20gives%20both%20theoretical%20and%20processual%20perspectives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20the%20colonial%20rulers%20built%20%E2%80%98civil%20stations%E2%80%99%20or%20(lines)%20and%20cantonments%20to%20bypass%20cities%20since%20the%2019th%20century%2C%20more%20particularly%20since%201857%2C%20is%20part%20of%20common%20knowledge%20of%20the%20urban%20studies%20in%20India.%20Another%20significant%20additions%20since%20the%20arrival%20of%20the%20railways%20in%20the%20mid-19th%20century%20were%20the%20railway%20colonies%2C%20so%20brilliantly%20captured%20by%20John%20Masters%20in%20his%20novel%20%3Cem%3EBhowani%20Junction.%3C%2Fem%3E%20King%20suggests%2C%20%E2%80%98The%20hill%20station%20was%20the%20third%20system%20in%20the%20urban%20system%20of%20the%20colonial%20community%3B%20its%20function%2C%20institutions%2C%20and%20form%20are%20to%20be%20understood%20within%20a%20framework%20which%20includes%20the%20civil%20station%20%E2%80%9Con%20the%20plains%E2%80%9D%20and%20urban%20developments%20%E2%80%9Cat%20home%E2%80%9D.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20explains%20the%20development%20of%20%E2%80%98hill%20stations%E2%80%99%20by%20reference%20to%20the%20three%20main%20variables%20of%20culture%2C%20technology%20and%20the%20dominance-dependence%20relationship%20of%20colonialism.%20It%20emerged%20as%20a%20socio-cultural%20organisation%20peculiar%20to%20colonialism.%C2%A0%20Evidently%2C%20they%20began%20as%20%E2%80%98health%20sanitaria%E2%80%99%20functioning%20as%20part%20of%20a%20British%20colonial%20eco-system.%20Darjeeling%E2%80%99s%20history%20clearly%20indicates%20this.%20Bhowali%20near%20Nainital%2C%20for%20example%2C%20was%20developed%20as%20a%20TB%20sanatorium.%20While%20Shimla%20with%20its%20Viceregal%20Lodge%20on%20Summer%20Hill%20was%20developed%20as%20the%20summer%20capital%20of%20the%20British%20empire%20in%20India%2C%20Nainital%20served%20the%20same%20purpose%20for%20United%20Provinces.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20not%20surprisingly%2C%20between%201815%20and%20independence%20of%20India%2C%20nearly%2080%20hill%20stations%20were%20developed%2C%20their%20elevations%20varying%20between%204%2C000%20and%208%2C000%20feet.%20As%20they%20proved%20convenient%20and%20useful%2C%20such%20urban%20settlements%20on%20hills%20were%20developed%20in%20lower%20mountain%20regions%2C%20clustered%20in%20four%20regions.%20Accessible%20to%20the%20European%20population%2C%20the%20Shimla-Mussoorie%20region%20had%20the%20largest%20number%20of%20them.%20The%20second%20cluster%20was%20developed%20in%20the%20northeast%20of%20India.%20Darjeeling%2C%20Shillong%20and%20some%20others.%20The%20Bombay%20Presidency%20also%20required%20a%20large%20number%20of%20European%20population%2C%20so%20the%20third%20cluster%20was%20developed%20in%20the%20Poona%20(now%20Pune)-Mahabaleshwar%20region.%20In%20the%20south%2C%20Ootacamunde%2C%20Kodaikanal%20and%20Coonoor%20were%20developed%20for%20the%20officers%20situated%20in%20the%20Madras%20Presidency.%20Thus%2C%20a%20number%20of%20well-developed%20for%20the%20European%20conditions%20urban%20settlement%20with%20office%20complexes%2C%C2%A0%20market%20to%20cater%20to%20the%20seasonal%20inflow%2C%20%E2%80%98public%E2%80%99%20schools%2C%20town%20hall%20and%20a%20club%2C%20were%20developed.%20All%20of%20them%20had%20a%20seasonal%20economy%2C%20so%20the%20process%20of%20urbaniSation%20was%20slow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPost-independence%20developments%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHill%20stations%20continued%20to%20be%20summer%20escape%20for%20the%20rich%20and%20the%20powerful%20in%20the%20country%20post-independence.%20Most%20hill%20stations%20had%20limited%20accessibility%20by%20the%20train%20system%20developed%20during%20the%20colonial%20era%20and%20roads%20that%20were%20not%20very%20welcoming.%20A%20tiny%20segment%20of%20the%20affluent%20could%20afford%20to%20travel%20by%20air%20partially%2C%20because%20all%20the%20hill%20stations%20did%20not%20have%20aerodrome.%20A%20family%20outing%20to%20the%20hills%20was%20neither%20in%20vogue%2C%20nor%20affordable%20for%20India%E2%80%99s%20tiny%20middle%20class.%20However%2C%20the%20hill%20vacation%20was%20middle-classised%20with%20its%20expansion%20since%20the%20mid-1980s%2C%20certainly%20since%20the%201990s.%20The%20leave%20travel%20grants%20in%20the%20government%20and%20the%20public%20sector%20added%20to%20it.%20The%20craving%20for%20it%20was%20heightened%20once%20India%20began%20turning%20into%20a%20%E2%80%98car%20society%E2%80%99%20around%20the%20same%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20the%20hill%20stations%20were%20for%20the%20elites%20and%20designed%20for%20a%20limited%20population%20settled%20there%20and%20a%20few%20thousand%20tourists%20trooping%20in%20during%20summer.%20With%20the%20need%20for%20more%20hotels%2C%20eateries%20and%20other%20tourist%20services%2C%20the%20need%20to%20expand%20infrastructure%20arose.%20That%20created%20requirements%20to%20upgrade%20roads%20for%20transport%20for%20automobiles.%20The%20increase%20in%20building%20activities%2C%20in%20which%20the%20local%20business%20and%20monied%20class%20also%20participated%2C%20resulted%20in%20denuding%20the%20hills%20of%20forests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShimla%2C%20for%20example%2C%20began%20as%20a%20city%20for%2025%2C000%20persons.%20In%202023%2C%20the%20population%20of%20Shimla%20metro%20region%20was%202%2C35%2C000.%C2%A0%20This%20is%20true%20of%20all%20the%20%E2%80%98hill%20stations%E2%80%99.%20Shimla%2C%20Mussoorie%2C%20Nainital%2C%20Bhimtal%2C%20Gangtok%2C%20Darjeeling%20and%20others%20lately%20are%20unable%20to%20take%20the%20inflow%20of%20tourist%20vehicles%20during%20summers.%20Even%20once%20quiet%20Manali%20has%20been%20reduced%20to%20concrete%20jungle.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20hills%20and%20their%20habitations%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20the%20hills%20have%20their%20habitations%20living%20there%20for%20generations.%20But%20they%20depended%20on%20nature%20and%20respected%20it.%C2%A0%20Concrete%20was%20rarely%20used%20for%20construction.%20Described%20as%20vernacular%20architecture%20in%20the%20language%20of%20architects%2C%20most%20building%20were%20constructed%20with%20local%20material.%20The%20maddening%20concretisation%20of%20the%20habitat%20copying%20the%20planes%20over%20decades%20became%20the%20bane%20of%20hill%20stations.%20Not%20only%20trees%20that%20held%20the%20hills%20erect%20were%20cut%20and%20removed%2C%20an%20extra%20burden%20of%20brick%20and%20concrete%20has%20been%20put%20on%20them%20in%20the%20past%20three%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20hills%20also%20situate%20a%20number%20of%20Hindu%20shrines.%20The%20lower%20Himalayas%20have%20glaciers%20that%20are%20sources%20of%20Ganga%20(Gangotri)%20and%20Yamuna%20(Yamunotri).%20Very%20few%20pilgrims%20used%20to%20visit%20them%20due%20to%20difficulty%20in%20travel%20and%20staying%20arrangements.%20Kedarnath%20and%20Badrinath%20are%20two%20of%20the%20holiest%20Hindu%20shrines%20in%20proximity.%20They%20also%20had%20limited%20pilgrim%20inflow.%20But%20due%20to%20the%20transport%20facilities%20and%20other%20infrastructure%20generally%20improving%20in%20the%20past%20two%20decades%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%20torrent%20of%20pilgrims%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202019%2C%20soon%20after%20his%20historic%20electoral%20victory%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20personally%20visited%20Kedarnath%20and%20stayed%20in%20a%20cave%20dwelling%20constructed%20there.%C2%A0%20In%202023%2C%20he%20announced%20the%20%3Cem%3EChar%20Dham%20Mahamarg%20Vikas%20Pariyojana%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethat%20also%20includes%20the%20extension%20and%20development%20of%20railway%20line%20to%20the%20farthest%20point.%20This%20was%20against%20the%20advice%20of%20the%20geologists%20and%20other%20experts%20of%20ecology.%20It%20had%20to%20have%20its%20impact.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20only%20do%20the%20hills%20need%20a%20sound%20habitat%20policy%2C%20they%20need%20rational%20and%20scientific%20development%20projects%20beyond%20electoral%20calculations%20to%20conserve%20them%20and%20make%20them%20sustainable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAjay%20K.%20Mehra%20is%20a%20political%20scientist.%20He%20was%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee%20Senior%20Fellow%2C%20Nehru%20Memorial%20Museum%20and%20Library%2C%20New%20Delhi%2C%202019-21%20and%20Principal%2C%20Shaheed%20Bhagat%20Singh%20Evening%20College%2C%20Delhi%20University%20(2018).%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693988618000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F06135212%2FCityscape_of_Shimla.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fthe-hills-werent-meant-for-rapid-development-and-so-the-cracks-are-starting-to-show%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Not%20only%20do%20the%20hills%20need%20a%20sound%20habitat%20policy%2C%20they%20need%20rational%20and%20scientific%20development%20projects%20beyond%20electoral%20calculations%20to%20conserve%20them%20and%20make%20them%20sustainable.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fthe-hills-werent-meant-for-rapid-development-and-so-the-cracks-are-starting-to-show%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22British%20couple%20trapped%20in%20Greek%20apartment%20for%2014%20hours%20as%20Storm%20Daniel%20turns%20res