20makes%20it%20clear%20that%20dharma%20is%20Varnashrama%20Dharma%20(%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%A3%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B6%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%82%20%E0%A4%A7%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AE%E0%A5%87%20%E0%A4%A8%E0%A4%B7%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%9F%E0%A5%87%20%E0%A4%B5%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%A6%E0%A4%AA%E0%A4%A5%E0%A5%87%20%E0%A4%A8%E0%A5%83%E0%A4%A3%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%82%20(12.2.12)).%20It%20says%20that%20those%20born%C2%A0%C2%A0from%20the%20%E2%80%98higher%E2%80%99%20organs%20of%20Virat%20Purusha%20are%20exalted%20and%20those%20born%20from%20inferior%20body%20parts%20of%20Virat%20Purusha%20are%20lowly%20(%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%A3%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%A8%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B6%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%A3%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%82%20%E0%A4%9A%20%E0%A4%9C%E0%A4%A8%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%AD%E0%A5%82%E0%A4%AE%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%A8%E0%A5%81%E0%A4%B8%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%A3%E0%A5%80%3A%2F%E0%A4%86%E0%A4%B8%E0%A4%A8%E0%A5%8D%20%E0%A4%AA%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%95%E0%A5%83%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%AF%E0%A5%8B%20%E0%A4%A8%E0%A5%83%E0%A4%A3%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%82%20%E0%A4%A8%E0%A5%80%E0%A4%9A%E0%A5%88%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%A8%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%9A%E0%A5%8B%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%AE%E0%A5%8B%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%83%2011.%2017.%2015%20).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20is%20varnashrama%20dharma%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESays%20Manusmriti%2C%20%E2%80%9CVarnasharama%20is%20the%20hereditary%20order%20of%20the%20four%20varnas%20and%20those%20who%20are%20products%20of%20permitted%20inter-Varna%20relationships%20(i.e.%2C%20antaralas%2C%20the%20product%20of%20anuloma%20relationships)%E2%80%9D%20(%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%B8%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%A8%E0%A5%8D%20%E0%A4%A6%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%B6%E0%A5%87%20%E0%A4%AF%20%E0%A4%86%E0%A4%9A%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B0%3A%20%E0%A4%AA%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%AE%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AA%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AF%20%E0%A4%95%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%97%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%83%2F%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%A3%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%A8%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%82%20%E0%A4%B8%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%A8%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B2%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%A8%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%82%20%E0%A4%B8%20%E0%A4%B8%E0%A4%A6%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%9A%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B0%20%E0%A4%89%E0%A4%9A%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%87%2C%20Manusmriti%202.18).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVarnashrama%20dharma%20imposes%20specific%20roles%20and%20duties%20on%20each%20varna.%20According%20to%20the%20Manusmriti%2C%C2%A0the%20Brahmin%E2%80%99s%20swadharma%20is%20study%2C%20teaching%2C%20yaajanam%20(receipt%20of%20gifts)%20and%20yajna%20(%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%9C%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%9E%C2%A0).%20In%20contrast%2C%20the%20duty%20of%20the%20Shudra%20is%20service%20of%20the%20Dvijas%20(%E0%A4%A6%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%9C%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%BF%C2%A0%E0%A4%B6%E0%A5%81%E0%A4%B6%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%82%E0%A4%B7%E0%A4%BE%C2%A0).%20A%20Shudra%20does%20not%20have%20the%20right%20to%20accumulate%20wealth%20or%20to%20engage%20in%20learning%20or%20any%20other%20activity.%20Chandalas%20(including%20out-castes%2C%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20our%20people)%20who%C2%A0%C2%A0are%20considered%20by%20authors%20of%C2%A0%20Dharmashastra%20as%20%E2%80%9Cwalking%20graveyards%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EVyavahara%20Mala%20%3C%2Fem%3E(there%20are%20various%20versions%2C%20this%20reference%20is%20to%20the%20version%20in%20the%20Thiruvananthapuram%20Ancient%20Manuscripts%20Library)%20treats%20the%20performance%20of%20occupations%20assigned%20to%20one%E2%80%99s%20varna%20as%20Dharma.%20It%20says%20that%20every%20one%20must%20engage%20only%20in%20the%20occupation%20of%20their%20varna.%20Performing%20the%20occupation%20of%20other%20varnas%20will%20only%20invite%20disaster%20(%E0%A4%B8%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B5%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%B7%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%AE%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%B5%20%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%A3%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%A8%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%82%20%E0%A4%8F%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%82%20%E0%A4%A7%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AE%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AF%E0%A5%8B%20%E0%A4%A7%E0%A4%A8%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%97%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%83%2F%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%AA%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%A6%E0%A4%A7%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%B8%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%A8%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%A8%20%E0%A4%9A%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%A6%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%AA%E0%A4%A6%E0%A5%8D%20%E0%A4%97%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%80%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%B8%E0%A5%80%20).%20As%20varna%20is%20acquired%20by%20birth%2C%20%3Cem%3EVyavahara%20Mala%3C%2Fem%3E%20holds%20that%20acquisition%20of%20a%20varna%20different%20from%20that%20into%20which%20one%20is%20born%2C%20by%20performing%20the%20occupation%20of%20a%20different%20varna%2C%20is%20a%20punishable%20offence.%20It%20commands%20kings%20to%20punish%20Shudras%20who%20wear%20sacred%20threads%20like%20Brahmins%20(%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%A8%E0%A5%8D%20%E0%A4%B8%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%A8%E0%A5%8D%20%E0%A4%96%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%A6%E0%A4%AF%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%A6%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%9C%E0%A4%BE%20%E0%A4%B6%E0%A5%82%E0%A4%A6%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%82%E0%A4%B6%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%9A%20%E0%A4%A6%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%9C%20%E0%A4%B2%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%82%E0%A4%97%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%A8%E0%A4%83)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShankaracharya%E2%80%99s%20Advaita%20philosophy%2C%20much%20admired%20as%20enlightened%2C%20accepts%20Chaturvanya.%20While%20interpreting%20the%20revelation%20in%20the%20Bhagvad%20Gita%20that%20God%20created%20chaturvanya%E2%80%9D%20(%E2%80%9C%E0%A4%9A%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%81%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%A3%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%82%20%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%BE%20%E0%A4%B8%E0%A5%83%E0%A4%B7%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%9F%E0%A4%82%E2%80%9D)%2C%20Shankaracharya%C2%A0says%20in%20his%C2%A0%3Cem%3EGita%20Bhashyam%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20the%20Purusha%20Sukta%20in%20the%20Rg%20Veda%20is%20correct%20%E2%80%94%20that%20humans%20are%20created%20by%20God%20in%20four%20varnas%20born%20from%20various%20organs%20of%20Virat%20Purusha%20in%20order%20of%20merit%2C%20%E2%80%9Cbrahmins%20from%20the%20face%2C%20etc%E2%80%9D.%2C%20leaving%20out%20the%20rest%20as%20sub-human%20(%E0%A4%9A%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B0%20%E0%A4%8F%E0%A4%B5%20%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%A3%E0%A4%BE%20%3A%20%E0%A4%9A%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%81%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%A3%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%82%20%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%BE%20%E0%A4%87%E0%A4%B6%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%A3%20%E0%A4%B8%E0%A5%83%E0%A4%B7%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%9F%E0%A4%82%20%E0%A4%89%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AA%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%A6%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%82%20%E0%A4%B5%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B9%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%A3%E0%A5%8B%20%E0%A4%B8%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AF%20%E0%A4%AE%E0%A5%81%E0%A4%96%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B8%E0%A5%80%E0%A4%A6%E0%A5%8D%20%E0%A4%87%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%A6%E0%A4%BF%20%E0%A4%B6%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%81%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%83).%20In%20Shankacharya%E2%80%99s%3Cem%3EBrihadaranyaka%20Upanishad%20Shankara%20Bhashyam%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20he%20accepts%20the%20varnashrama%20division%20and%20interprets%20the%20word%20%E2%80%9CBrahma%E2%80%9D%20as%20meaning%20%E2%80%98the%20source%20of%20protection%20of%20the%20pride%20of%20the%20Brahmin%20caste%E2%80%99%20(%E0%A4%AC%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B9%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%A3%20%E0%A4%9C%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%AD%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%A8%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%8D%20%E0%A4%AC%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%B9%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AE%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%AD%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%A7%E0%A5%80%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%87%2C%201.%204.%2011).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArthashastra%20warns%20that%20if%20this%20dharma%20is%20violated%2C%20the%20result%20will%20be%20a%20world%20with%20abhorrent%20hybrid%20and%20impure%20races%20(%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%B8%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%BF%20%E0%A4%95%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%AE%E0%A5%87%20%E0%A4%B2%E0%A5%8B%E0%A4%95%E0%A4%83%20%E0%A4%B8%E0%A4%99%E0%A4%95%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%A6%E0%A5%81%E0%A4%9A%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%9B%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%A7%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AF%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%87).Manu%20holds%20that%20varna%20hybridisation%20occurs%20through%20prohibited%20intermarriage%20and%20inter-relationships%20between%20varnas%20where%20the%20varna%20order%20is%20abandoned%20(%E0%A4%B5%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%AD%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%9A%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%A3%20%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%A3%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%A8%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%B5%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%A6%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%BE%20%E0%A4%B5%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%A6%E0%A4%A8%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%A8%20%E0%A4%9A%2F%E0%A4%B8%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%95%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%A3%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%82%20%E0%A4%9A%20%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%97%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%A8%20%E0%A4%9C%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%A8%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%87%20%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%A3%20%E0%A4%B8%E0%A4%99%E0%A4%95%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%83).%20Manu%20also%20holds%20that%20wherever%20there%20is%20inter-mingling%20of%20varnas%2C%20the%20purity%20of%20varna%20is%20destroyed%20and%20the%20country%20will%20perish%20along%20with%20the%20inhabitants%20of%20the%20country%20(%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B0%20%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B5%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%87%20%E0%A4%AA%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%A7%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%82%E0%A4%B8%E0%A4%BE%20%E0%A4%9C%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%A8%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%87%20%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%A3%20%E0%A4%A6%E0%A5%81%E0%A4%B7%E0%A4%95%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%83%2F%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B7%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%9F%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%95%E0%A5%88%E0%A4%83%20%E0%A4%B8%E0%A4%B9%20%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%A6%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B7%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%9F%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%82%20%E0%A4%95%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B7%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%AA%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%AE%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%B5%20%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%A8%E0%A4%B6%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%BF%C2%A0%20Manu%20.%2010.%2016%20).%20In%20the%20Bhagwad%20Gita%2C%20Arjuna%20also%20worries%20that%20the%20caste%20will%20perish%20due%20to%20marriages%20that%20violate%20the%20caste%20order%20(Gita%2C%201.40).%20The%20%3Cem%3EBhagavada%20Puranam%3C%2Fem%3E%20says%20that%20Lord%20Vasudeva%20will%20reincarnate%20to%20protect%20varnashramadharma%20when%20it%20starts%20to%20be%20destroyed%20(%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%B9%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AF%E0%A5%88%20%E0%A4%95%E0%A4%B2%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%A8%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%87%C2%A0%20%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B8%E0%A5%81%E0%A4%A6%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%A8%E0%A5%81%20%E0%A4%B6%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%95%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B7%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%8C%2F%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%A3%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B6%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%AF%E0%A5%81%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%82%20%E0%A4%A7%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AE%E0%A4%82%20%E0%A4%AA%E0%A5%82%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%B5%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AA%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%B0%E0%A4%A5%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%BF%E0%A4%B7%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%AF%E0%A4%A4%E0%A5%87%2C%2012.%203%20.%2038).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20therefore%20beyond%20question%20that%20what%20the%20Dharmashastra%20and%20Purana%20texts%20define%20and%20interpret%20as%20Dharma%2C%20and%20what%20is%20meant%20by%20sanatana%20dharma%2C%20is%20varnashrama%20dharma%2C%20the%20duty%20to%20eternally%20maintain%20the%20varnashrama%20social%20order%20and%20world-view.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20January%201950%20lecture%20delivered%20in%20Sivagiri%2C%20Kerala%2C%20the%20renowned%20Kerala%20social%20reformer%20and%20thinker%20%E2%80%9CSahodaran%E2%80%9D%20Ayyappan%2C%20disciple%20of%20Narayana%20Guru%2C%20specifically%20warned%20that%20the%20caste%20system%20is%20being%20promoted%20under%20the%20guise%20of%20%E2%80%9CDharma%E2%80%9D.%20Ayyappan%20wrote%20in%20his%20poem%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EParivatanam%3C%2Fem%3E%20(Change)%E2%80%99%20that%20what%20goes%20under%20names%20such%20as%20%E2%80%9Csanatana%20dharma%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cvarnashrama%E2%80%9D%20dharma%20is%20the%20religion%20built%20by%20the%20Brahmins%20which%20lowers%20the%20other%20(those%20who%20are%20not%20Savarnas)%20as%20inferior.%20In%20an%20address%20presented%20to%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20during%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20visit%20to%20Kerala%20in%201934%2C%20Sahodaran%20said%20that%20it%20is%20this%20%E2%80%9Ccruel%E2%80%9D%20dharma%20called%20varnashramadharma%20that%20makes%20people%20in%20India%20destitute.%20Dr%20B.R.%20Ambedkar%20wrote%2C%20%E2%80%9CVedas%20and%20Shastras%2C%20which%20reject%20rationality%20and%20reject%20morality%2C%20should%20be%20destroyed%20with%20dynamite%2C%E2%80%9D%20because%20the%20Vedas%20and%20Dharmashastras%20are%20the%20foundational%20precepts%20of%20maintaining%20the%20caste-violent%20hierarchical%20social%20system%20of%20varnashrama%20dharma.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENarayana%20Guru%2C%20Sahodaran%20Ayyappan%2C%20Periyar%20and%20Ambedkar%20courageously%20rejected%20the%20attempt%20to%20strengthen%20the%20caste%20system%20by%20disguising%20it%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98glorious%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%9Csanatana%E2%80%9D%20tradition.%20Having%20embraced%20Buddhism%20along%20with%20his%20lakhs%20of%20followers%2C%20Ambedkar%20totally%20rejected%20sanatana%20dharma%2C%20unfazed%20by%20violent%20attacks%20by%20Brahmanist%20ideology.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmbedkar%20must%20be%20our%20guiding%20light%20in%20understanding%20what%20%E2%80%9Csanatana%20dharma%E2%80%9D%20is%20today%20%E2%80%93%20nothing%20more%20than%20a%20re-branding%20of%20the%20inhuman%20and%20anti-social%20caste%20system%2C%20intended%20to%20maintain%20and%20strengthen%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDr%20T.S.%20Syam%20Kumar%20holds%20a%20doctorate%20in%20Sanskrit%20Literature%20from%20the%20Sree%20Sankaracharya%20Sanskrit%20University%2C%20Kalady%2C%20Kerala.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Malayalam%20version%20of%20this%20article%20was%20first%20published%20by%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsuprabhaatham.com%2Fdr-ts-syam-kumar-about-sanatan-dharma%2F%3Ffbclid%3DIwAR3GiBe0HA_FAliGEj_HPeZVHWeLlXVlRF6q4m0lApdGn-t2XyoCuliqH7E%5C%22%3ESuprabhaatham%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%