o%20Himachal%20as%20they%20wanted%20to%20live%20in%20the%20hills%20and%20do%20something%20of%20their%20own%3B%20Picture%20credit%3A%20Kartik%20Budhraja%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20couple%20fell%20in%20love%20with%20the%20place%20and%20wanted%20to%20move%20there.%20At%20that%20time%2C%20Anuradha%20and%20Kartik%20were%20working%20as%20media%20professionals%20in%20Singapore.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20urge%20to%20come%20back%20to%20India%20was%20mainly%20for%20two%20reasons.%20Firstly%2C%20we%20both%20wanted%20to%20get%20out%20of%20the%20rat%20race%20and%20build%20a%20business%20of%20our%20own%2C%20and%20secondly%2C%20we%20loved%20the%20mountains%20and%20nature%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20recalls.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAfter%20a%20few%20years%20of%20planning%20and%20iterating%2C%20we%20decided%20to%20finally%20make%20the%20move.%20We%20quit%20our%20jobs%20and%20decided%20to%20move%20to%20Himachal%20Pradesh%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20duo%20moved%20to%20Thanedar%20and%20started%20a%20fruit%20jam%20business%20utilising%20the%20fruits%20in%20the%20area.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAfter%20setting%20up%20the%20factory%20and%20settling%20ourselves%20in%20the%20environment%2C%20we%20really%20wanted%20to%20have%20a%20permanent%20home.%20By%202017%2C%20we%20were%20actively%20looking%20for%20a%20suitable%20place%2C%E2%80%9D%20recalls%20Kartik.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYears%20later%20in%202017%2C%20at%20the%20same%20annual%20%3Cem%3Emela%20%3C%2Fem%3Ein%20Thanedar%2C%20the%20couple%20found%20their%20dream%20home.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COur%20girls%20wanted%20to%20set%20up%20a%20stall%20of%20our%20jams%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3Emela%3C%2Fem%3E.%20One%20of%20the%20farmers%20from%20Saroga%20village%20came%20up%20to%20us%20and%20asked%20why%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20make%20cherry%20jams.%20Jokingly%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%E2%80%98if%20we%20come%20to%20his%20village%20he%20would%20give%20us%20cherries%E2%80%99%2C%E2%80%9D%20recalls%20Anuradha.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20response%2C%20I%20said%20that%20we%20will%20buy%20cherries%20only%20if%20he%20gets%20us%20a%20house%20in%20his%20village.%20All%20we%20know%20is%20that%20the%20next%20day%2C%20we%20are%20driving%20up%20to%20the%20village%2C%20meeting%20the%20same%20farmer%20again%20and%20looking%20at%20the%20land%20that%20was%20to%20become%20our%20home%2C%E2%80%9D%20adds%20Anuradha.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20840px)%20100vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fsaroga-woods-2-1-1693576393.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20pictures%20of%20the%20house%20when%20covered%20in%20snow%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fsaroga-woods-2-1-1693576393.jpg%20840w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fsaroga-woods-2-1-1693576393-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fsaroga-woods-2-1-1693576393-500x261.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fsaroga-woods-2-1-1693576393-768x401.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fsaroga-woods-2-1-1693576393-150x78.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-328889%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22439%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20house%20has%20a%20rainwater%20harvesting%20system%20and%20solar%20panels%20to%20provide%20electricity%20to%20the%20house%3B%20Picture%20credit%3A%20Kartik%20Budhraja%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDescribing%20the%20land%2C%20Kartik%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20everything%20we%20had%20dreamt%20of.%20It%20stood%208000%20sq%20ft%20above%20sea%20level%20with%20an%20amazing%20view%20of%20the%20Himalayas%20on%20one%20side%20and%20the%20Satluj%20River%20on%20the%20other.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20duo%20decided%20to%20purchase%20the%20land%20and%20hence%20began%20the%20journey%20of%20making%20their%20dream%20home.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Waking%20up%20to%20the%20Himalayas%20in%20our%20nature-friendly%20home%E2%80%99%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20land%20was%20only%20six%20kilometres%20from%20our%20factory%20and%20on%20three%20elevations.%20We%20decided%20not%20to%20touch%20the%20natural%20beauty%20of%20it%20and%20instead%20build%20our%20home%20around%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBuilt%20on%20three%20levels%2C%20the%20house%20has%20three%20bedrooms%2C%20three%20bathrooms%2C%20one%20parlour%20room%20and%20a%20living%20room.%20Along%20with%20a%20dining%20room%20and%20a%20kitchen%2C%20it%20also%20has%20a%20pantry%2C%20a%20gym%2C%20a%20library%20and%20a%20lounge.%20The%20house%20has%20its%20own%20storeroom%2C%20an%20attic%2C%20and%20quarters%20for%20domestic%20help.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20did%20not%20want%20to%20disturb%20the%20shape%20and%20nature%20of%20the%20land%20and%20decided%20to%20not%20level%20it.%20The%20house%2C%20if%20you%20look%20at%20it%20from%20the%20outside%2C%20does%20not%20look%20like%20an%20eyesore%20on%20the%20beautiful%20hill.%20Instead%2C%20it%20blends%20with%20nature%20and%20actually%20looks%20like%20a%20part%20of%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20philosophy%20of%20the%20couple%20behind%20building%20the%20house%20was%20simple%20%E2%80%94%20they%20wanted%20it%20to%20be%20efficient%2C%20cosy%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F187566%2Fchennai-architect-sustainable-homes-eco-friendly-construction-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eand%20nature-friendly.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMy%20wife%20and%20I%20were%20the%20sole%20designers%20of%20the%20house.%20We%20did%20everything%20from%20scratch.%20We%20wanted%20the%20house%20to%20be%20comfortable%20and%20nature-friendly%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fsaroga-woods-3-1693576553.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22All%20the%20materials%20used%20in%20the%20house%20are%20sourced%20locally%20to%20improve%20the%20local%20economy%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fsaroga-woods-3-1693576553.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fsaroga-woods-3-1693576553-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fsaroga-woods-3-1693576553-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fsaroga-woods-3-1693576553-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fsaroga-woods-3-1693576553-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-328892%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EAll%20the%20materials%20used%20in%20the%20house%20are%20sourced%20locally%20contributing%20to%20the%20local%20economy%3B%20Picture%20credit%3A%20Kartik%20Budhraja%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExplaining%20the%20various%20sustainable%20features%20of%20the%20house%2C%20Kartik%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20studied%20the%20area%20and%20land%20very%20well.%20We%20wanted%20to%20have%20a%20carbon%20negative%2C%20water%20efficient%20and%20climate-resistant%20home.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAll%20the%20materials%20used%20in%20the%20house%20are%20sourced%20locally%20as%20we%20wanted%20to%20contribute%20to%20the%20local%20economy.%20The%20bricks%20used%20in%20the%20construction%20of%20the%20house%20were%20fly%20ash%20bricks.%20We%20used%20them%20as%20they%20have%20a%20lesser%20carbon%20footprint%20and%20are%20more%20energy%20efficient%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20keep%20the%20house%20energy%20efficient%2C%20the%20couple%20installed%20solar%20power%20in%20their%20home.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20an%208%20KW%20solar%20plant%20set%20up%20to%20produce%2072%20to%2080%20percent%20of%20the%20power%20needs%20of%20the%20house.%20Additionally%2C%20we%20also%20have%20a%20rainwater%20harvesting%20plant%20set%20up.%20We%20catch%20about%2030%2C000%20litres%20of%20water%20in%20our%20underground%20water%20storage%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20house%20also%20believes%20in%20zero%20waste%20and%20has%20a%20water%20filtration%20system.%20%E2%80%9CAll%20our%20grey%20water%20(the%20dirty%20but%20reusable%20water%20from%20sinks%2C%20washing%20machines)%20is%20filtered%20and%20is%20used%20in%20cleaning%20and%20drinking.%20Even%20the%20wood%20packaging%20in%20which%20our%20windows%20and%20doors%20came%20were%20used%20to%20make%20some%20sort%20of%20furniture%20so%20that%20nothing%20goes%20to%20waste%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20house%20also%20has%20double%20glazing%20in%20the%20windows%20to%20keep%20it%20warm%20during%20the%20winter.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20their%20effort%20to%20combine%20traditional%20and%20contemporary%20elements%20in%20their%20home%2C%20the%20Budhrajas%20acquired%20all%20of%20their%20wood%20from%20a%20%3Cem%3Ekabadiya%C2%A0%20%3C%2Fem%3E(scrap%20dealer)%20who%20sources%20the%20wood%20from%20dismantled%20and%20ageing%20government%20and%20residential%20structures%20in%20Himachal%20Pradesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20believe%20in%20reusing%20and%20upcycling.%20The%20wood%20in%20some%20of%20our%20doors%20is%20nearly%20100%20years%20old%2C%E2%80%9D%20informs%20Anuradha.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20also%20used%20the%20Himalayan%20Black%20State%2C%20a%20type%20of%20tile%20local%20to%20the%20state%2C%20for%20the%20flooring%20and%20cladding%20of%20the%20house.%20It%20is%20a%20great%20conductor%20of%20heat.%20We%20also%20use%20electrical%20heating%20using%20solar%20power%20to%20keep%20the%20house%20warm%20for%20the%20harsh%20winters%2C%E2%80%9D%20adds%20Anuradha.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-instgrm-version%3D%5C%2214%5C%22%20data-instgrm-permalink%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FCkyB8k4SRwt%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26amp%3Butm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FCkyB8k4SRwt%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26utm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3EView%20this%20post%20on%20Instagram%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FCkyB8k4SRwt%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26utm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EA%20post%20shared%20by%20Saroga%20Woods%20Home%20Stay%20(%40sarogawoods)%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%5Cn%3Cp%3ECladding%20is%20a%20method%20in%20which%20the%20same%20tiles%20are%20used%20on%20the%20walls%20of%20the%20house%20from%20the%20outside%20to%20keep%20them%20insulated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20house%20also%20has%20a%20kitchen%20garden%20where%20the%20couple%20