2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThereafter%2C%20oil%20is%20extracted%20from%20these%20seeds%20on%20a%20stone%20mill%20with%20a%20wooden%20pestle.%20Usually%2C%20during%20the%20refined%20oil%20processing%2C%20the%20hydrogenation%20temperatures%20go%20up%20to%20200%20degree%20Celsius.%20While%20this%20is%20done%20to%20increase%20the%20shelf%20life%20of%20oils%2C%20the%20process%20also%20yields%20trans%20fats%2C%20which%20severely%20increase%20cardiovascular%20risks%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%202022%20study%20by%20the%20%3Cem%3EInternational%20Journal%20of%20Food%20and%20Nutritional%20Sciences%3C%2Fem%3E%20reveals%20that%20because%20of%20this%20procedure%2C%20the%20seeds%20are%20stripped%20of%20all%20naturally%20occurring%20nutrients%20and%20antioxidants%2C%20resulting%20in%20a%20final%20product%20that%20is%20devoid%20of%20flavour%20and%20offers%20no%20positive%20effects%20on%20our%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20just%20crush%20seeds%20hard%20enough%20to%20bring%20as%20much%20oil%20and%20leave%20the%20rest.%20We%20make%20sure%20that%20we%20do%20not%20exceed%2050%20degrees%20Celsius.%20For%20us%2C%20it%20does%20come%20up%20with%20a%20cost%20as%20our%20extraction%20percentages%20are%20low.%20But%20that%20is%20how%20our%20oils%20get%20better%20in%20aroma%20and%20health%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Yaseen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20extraction%20process%2C%20oil%20is%20passed%20through%20a%20cotton%20filter%20system%20to%20remove%20seed%20sediments%20from%20the%20oil.%20Lastly%2C%20the%20cold-pressed%20oils%20are%20packaged%20in%20opaque%20gable-top%20paperboard%20cartons.%20%E2%80%9COur%20opaque%20packaging%20unlike%20PET%20and%20glass%20bottles%20keep%20the%20oil%20fresh%20for%20a%20long%20time%20and%20prevents%20rancidity%20that%20is%20caused%20by%20exposure%20to%20sunlight%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5